\subsection{Valence effects are specific to alcohol craving}

Next, we tested whether exposure to pro- vs. anti-alcohol information was specifically associated with an increase in alcohol craving rather than a general appetite for beverages (H2). Study 2 results show that the main effect of valence is specific to trials in which participants rated their craving for alcoholic (rather than non-alcoholic) drinks, confirming H2 (see Figure ~\ref{fig:specificityPlot}). In fact, pro-alcohol messaging actually decreased craving for non-alcoholic drinks compared to anti-alcohol messages.

